com.soebes.subversion.sapm
Class AccessRulesGroupGroupFromConfigFileWithAliasesTest

java.lang.Object
  com.soebes.subversion.sapm.TestBase
      com.soebes.subversion.sapm.AccessRulesGroupGroupFromConfigFileWithAliasesTest

public class AccessRulesGroupGroupFromConfigFileWithAliasesTest
extends TestBase

This test will create access rules which are read from configuration file (svnaccess-aliases.conf) and the same as already defined in the AccessRulesGroupGroupTest file. This will make sure that the object tree which has been read via the parser is the same as it would be if it had been created manually as in AccessRulesGroupGroupTest. The following rules are read from the configuration file (svnaccess-aliases.conf). 

 [aliases]
 harry = CN=Harold Hacker,OU=Engineers,DC=red-bean,DC=com
 sally = CN=Sally Swatterbug,OU=Engineers,DC=red-bean,DC=com
 joe = CN=Gerald I. Joseph,OU=Engineers,DC=red-bean,DC=com

 [groups]
 c-developer = &harry, brian
 d-developer = michael, &sally
 e-developer = &joe
 all-developer = @c-developer, @d-developer, @e-developer

 [/]
 * = r
 [repository:/project-c/trunk]
 @c-developer = rw
 [repository:/project-d/trunk]
 @d-developer = rw
 [repository:/project-e/trunk]
 @e-developer = rw
 [global:/project/trunk]
 @all-developer = rw
The tests will check if the AccessLevel will be extracted correctly and furthermore if the access to different directories inside this repository will work well.

Author:
Karl Heinz Marbaise
